genresAdvancedInfo.name: outer hip hop
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Outer hip hop is a subgenre of hip hop that is characterized by its experimental and avant-garde approach to music. It is often associated with artists who push the boundaries of traditional hip hop, incorporating elements of electronic, jazz, or rock music into their sound. Outer hip hop is known for its abstract and unconventional beats, as well as its socially conscious lyrics that tackle themes such as identity, race, and politics.
